Package kcn.methodreferencing

Class MethodReference

  • java.lang.Object
    • kcn.methodreferencing.MethodReference
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IMethodReference
    public class MethodReference
extends java.lang.Object
implements IMethodReference
    Class instances hold a reference to *a Method object and an Object object* and, is able to execute the method on the object . The Reference has a generic twin in MeReference, which is safer to use and has much greater flexibility.

    NB. Naming of run methods is mechanical and I don't really like it, but didn't come up with something better yet.

      • run_paramT_reT

        public <T> T run_paramT_reT​(T inputParameter)
        Method returns the result of the referenced method, - called/executed method is ONLY able to and MUST return an object of the same type as it's parameter type T.
        Parameters:
        inputParameter - object type T whose value will be used as parameter when executing referenced method.
        Returns:

      • run_paramT_reObj

        public <T> java.lang.Object run_paramT_reObj​(T inputParameter)
        Method executes the method referenced, returns a type Object object; so if you choose this method, you must cast the return.
        Parameters:
        inputParameter - object type T whose value will be used as parameter when executing referenced method.
        Returns:
        object type Object

      • run_paramTU_reObj

        public <T,​U> java.lang.Object run_paramTU_reObj​(T inputT,
                                                      U inputU)
        Method 'runs/invokes' methodToExecute with parameter of type T and U and returns an object of type Object.

        This is not safe, or maybe even smart - but it might be used in clever ways!

        NB: this seems like a bad idea to me, but also something some people might do. But I recommend the generic version for most tasks.

        Parameters:
        inputT - input parameter type T -
        inputU - input parameter type U argued object used *only* to get return *type*.
        Returns:
        object type Object
